                      <span>2000-06-15</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>The book is divided into two parts corresponding roughly to undergraduate material and graduate.  The selection of topics is robust; the writing is clear and consise.  The level is senior and above.  The reader should have  some knowledge of advanced math such as group theory, and analysis of  algorithms.  Great book! One of the best ever!</span>
                  
              
